 characters in the [[Teletoon (Canadian TV channel)|Teletoon]] Canadian animated sitcom ''[[Stoked (TV series)|Stoked]]''\n* Emma,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.supernaturalwiki.com/index.php?title=Emma|title=Emma \u2013 Super-wiki|publisher=}}</ref> the Amazon daughter of [[Dean Winchester]] from the television series ''[[Supernatural (American TV series)|Supernatural]]''\n* [[M\u00f6lders (Emma)|Emma]], the main character in ''[[Emma: A Victorian Romance]]''\n* Emma Bloom, peculiar girl in Ransom Rigg's series ''[[Miss Peregrine's Home for Peculiar Children]]''\n* [[Emma Brooker]], a character from the British soap opera ''[[Coronation Street]]''\n* Emma Bovary, the heroine of [[Gustave Flaubert]]'s novel ''[[Madame Bovary]]''\n* [[Emma Carstairs]], a character and protagonist in [[Cassandra Clare]]'s ''[[The Shadowhunter Chronicles]]'' and heroine in ''[[The Dark Artifices]]''\n* Emma Coolidge in ''[[Heroes (American TV series)|Heroes]]''\n* [[Emma Frost]] in [[Marvel Comics]]\n* [[Characters of Friends#Emma Geller Green|Emma Geller-Green]], daughter of Rachel Green and Ross Geller on ''[[Friends]]''\n* Emma Gilbert in ''[[H2O: Just Add Water|H<sub>2</sub>O: Just Add Water]]''\n* Emma Goodall, the pink ranger in ''[[Power Rangers Megaforce]]''\n* Emma Kliesen, a minor character in the [[Tekken Tag Tournament 2|Tekken]] series\n* Emma Karn, a main character in the NBC series ''[[Aquarius (American TV series)|Aquarius]]''\n* [[Emma Nelson]], the staple character in ''[[Degrassi: The Next Generation]]''\n* [[Emma Peel]], fictional television spy played by [[Diana Rigg]] in the British 1960s adventure series ''[[The Avengers (TV series)|The Avengers]]''\n* [[Emma Pillsbury]] in ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''\n* Emma Ross on the Disney Channel series ''[[Jessie (2011 TV series)|Jessie]]'', and ''[[Bunk'd]]''\n* [[Emma Sheen]], Gundam pilot from the AEUG group in the anime series ''[[Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam]]''\n* [[Emma Swan]], protagonist of the television series ''[[